North Korean news media on Thursday said the communist nation's military is on full alert for war with the United States if a dispute over nuclear inspections comes to blows.
The North's official Korean Central News Agency reported that North Korean soldiers and people of all walks of life were ``on full alert for war''.
North Korea typically sends out belligerent rhetoric, especially when it enters high-stake talks with Washington.
The United States and North Korea are set to resume talks Friday about inspections of an underground North Korean site suspected of being used to produce nuclear weapons.
